#Text=Randazza argues in the response filed on behalf of Eiland-Hall that Beck is using the process of the WIPO court to infringe the free speech rights of his client ;  Beck is attempting to use this transnational body to circumvent and subvert the Respondent 's constitutional rights [ to freedom of speech ] , " he wrote .

column1: #Text=Randazza cites the U.S. Supreme Court case , Hustler Magazine v. Falwell , in arguing that Beck 's attorneys advised him against filing legal action in a U.S. court because the website would likely be seen as a form of parody and due to the First Amendment to the U.S. Constitution , such legal action would not be successful .

#Text=On September 29 , Randazza sent a request to Beck 's representatives , asking that their client agree to stipulate to the United States Constitution , and especially to the First Amendment , during the case before the WIPO .

#Text=In the request , Randazza quotes a statement from Beck himself about the usage of international law by United States citizens , Beck said , " [ o]nce we sign our rights over to international law , the Constitution is officially dead .

#Text= Randazza wrote in the request , " I am certain that neither party wishes to see First Amendment rights subordinated to international trademark principles , thus unwittingly proving Mr. Beck 's point .

column1: #Text=Lest this case become an example of international law causing damage to the constitutional rights that both of our clients hold dear , I respectfully request that your client agree to stipulate to the application of American constitutional law to this case .
